member.name: T:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType
member.summary: Supported modes for rendering the 3D images.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.Solid
member.summary: Displays textured and lit geometric shapes. The auxiliary color is ignored.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.SolidWireframe
member.summary: Displays textured and lit geometric shapes (triangles) with single color edges on top of them. The color of these edges is determined by the auxiliary color.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.Transparent
member.summary: Displays textured and lit geometric shapes (triangles) with an added level of transparency. The auxiliary color is ignored.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.TransparentWireframe
member.summary: Displays textured and lit geometric shapes (triangles) with an added level of transparency, with single color opaque edges on top of it. The color of these edges is determined by the auxiliary color.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.BoundingBox
member.summary: Displays the bounding box edges of each node. The color of the bounding box edges is determined by the auxiliary color.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.TransparentBoundingBox
member.summary: Displays bounding boxes faces of each node with an added level of transparency. The color of the bounding box faces is determined by the face color.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.TransparentBoundingBoxOutline
member.summary: Displays bounding boxes edges and faces of each node with an added level of transparency. The color of the bounding box edges is determined by the auxiliary color. The color of the bounding boxes faces is determined by the face color.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.Wireframe
member.summary: Displays only edges in a single color. The color of these edges is determined by the auxiliary color.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.ShadedWireframe
member.summary: Displays only edges and applies lighting. The auxiliary color is ignored.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.HiddenWireframe
member.summary: Displays edges in a single color, though removes back-facing and obscured edges. The color of these edges is determined by the auxiliary color.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.Vertices
member.summary: Displays only vertices in a single color. The color of these points is determined by the auxiliary color.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.ShadedVertices
member.summary: Displays only vertices, though uses their vertex color and applies lighting. The auxiliary color is ignored.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.Illustration
member.summary: Displays silhouette edges with surfaces, removes obscured lines. The color of these edges is determined by the auxiliary color, and the color of the surfaces is determined by the face color.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.SolidOutline
member.summary: Displays silhouette edges with lit and textured surfaces, removes obscured lines. The color of these edges is determined by the auxiliary color.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.Annotations.PDF3DRenderModeType.ShadedIllustration
member.summary: Displays silhouette edges with lit and textured surfaces and an additional emissive term to remove poorly lit areas of the artwork. The color of these edges is determined by the auxiliary color.

member.summary: Before edge of the first child's allocation rectangle aligned with that of the table cell's content rectangle.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.LogicalStructure.PDFStandardLayoutBlockAlign.Middle
member.summary: Children centred within the table cell. The distance between the before edge of the first child's allocation rectangle and that of the table cell's content rectangle shall be the same as the distance between the after edge of the last child's allocation rectangle and that of the table cell's content rectangle.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.LogicalStructure.PDFStandardLayoutBlockAlign.After
member.summary: After edge of the last child's allocation rectangle aligned with that of the table cell's content rectangle.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.LogicalStructure.PDFStandardLayoutBlockAlign.Justify
member.summary: Children aligned with both the before and after edges of the table cell's content rectangle. The first child shall be placed as described for and the last child as described for , with equal spacing between the children. If there is only one child, it shall be aligned with the before edge only, as for .

member.summary:

Supported in PDF/UA-1.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.LogicalStructure.PDFStandardStructureTypes.Note
member.summary:
An item of explanatory text, such as a footnote or an endnote, that is referred to from within the body of the document. It may have a label (structure type ) as a child. The note may be included as a child of the structure element in the body text that refers to it, or it may be included elsewhere (such as in an endnotes section) and accessed by means of a reference (structure type ).
Tagged PDF does not prescribe the placement of footnotes in the page content order. They may be either inline or at the end of the page, at the discretion of theconforming writer.
Supported in PDF/UA-1.

Supported in PDF/UA-1.

An inline portion of text attributed to someone other than the author of the surrounding text.
The quoted text should be contained inline within a single paragraph. This differs from the block-level element , which consists of one or more complete paragraphs (or other elements presented as if they were complete paragraphs).
Supported in PDF/UA-1.

member.name: F:O2S.Components.PDF4NET.LogicalStructure.PDFStandardStructureTypes.TableOfContents
member.summary:
A list made up of table of contents item entries () and/or other nested table of contents entries ().
A entry that includes only entries represents a flat hierarchy. A entry that includes other nested entries (and possibly entries) represents a more complex hierarchy. Ideally, the hierarchy of a top level entry reflects the structure of the main body of the document.
